WEBVTT

01:51.744 --> 01:53.812
- Bang bang, bang bang!

02:41.895 --> 02:44.763
Bang bang!

02:44.765 --> 02:46.498
Ferris, you're
supposed to be dead!

02:46.500 --> 02:48.667
- Hey hey, Jamison, Ferris.

02:48.669 --> 02:51.470
Come on boys, take
it easy, would you?

02:51.472 --> 02:52.871
- He's being stupid!

02:52.873 --> 02:54.306
- Hey!

02:54.308 --> 02:56.175
What did I tell you
about using that word?

02:56.177 --> 03:00.479
We don't call each other
names in this family, do we?

03:00.481 --> 03:01.280
- No sir.

03:01.282 --> 03:02.381
- All right.

03:02.383 --> 03:03.615
- You're supposed
to say special.

03:03.617 --> 03:04.816
- Now play nice together

03:04.818 --> 03:06.752
or you're not gonna
play together at all.

03:07.887 --> 03:08.820
- Yes sir.

03:08.822 --> 03:11.256
All right, let's play fair.

03:11.258 --> 03:14.259
- Okay but when I shoot
you, you go down like this.

03:14.261 --> 03:14.860
Bang bang!

03:14.862 --> 03:17.196
- Oh, you got me.

03:17.198 --> 03:18.530
- Hooray!

03:19.332 --> 03:20.933
- Who wants iced tea?

03:20.935 --> 03:22.968
- I'm thirsty, let's go kids!

03:22.970 --> 03:24.436
Come on.

03:48.761 --> 03:50.762
Jamison where's your brother?

03:50.764 --> 03:51.830
- I don't know.

03:51.832 --> 03:53.465
- He was right here.

03:53.467 --> 03:55.267
- He went that way.

03:56.803 --> 03:57.903
- Ferris!

04:04.377 --> 04:05.544
Ferris?

04:07.380 --> 04:08.513
Ferris!

04:19.926 --> 04:21.392
Ferris!

04:27.033 --> 04:28.467
Ferris, wait!

04:28.469 --> 04:29.534
Wait!

04:32.772 --> 04:33.972
Ferris!

04:44.684 --> 04:46.785
- Hey, you're on
private property.

04:46.787 --> 04:48.487
Hands where I can see them.

04:48.489 --> 04:49.554
- He's got a gun!

04:50.791 --> 04:52.424
- Ferris, no!

04:55.862 --> 04:56.895
No!

05:39.372 --> 05:40.939
- Yeah well, I've had
enough wild nights

05:40.941 --> 05:42.741
to last me a few lifetimes.

05:42.743 --> 05:44.943
And they'll be around
for three or four more,

05:44.945 --> 05:46.345
you know what I mean?

05:46.347 --> 05:47.579
- I think I do.

05:47.581 --> 05:49.481
- Not yet, sweetie.

05:49.483 --> 05:53.018
Look, when I started this band
it was all about the music.

05:53.020 --> 05:55.821
Now it seems to be
just one huge party

05:55.823 --> 05:57.989
sort of blended together.

05:59.559 --> 06:01.660
You doing anything tonight?

06:01.662 --> 06:03.562
- Um, I don't know.

06:05.932 --> 06:07.933
- Well, have you
seen my trailer?

06:07.935 --> 06:10.001
- We're just warming
them up for you.

06:12.505 --> 06:15.140
- Um Trent, we
need you on stage.

06:15.142 --> 06:16.541
Now.

06:17.377 --> 06:19.444
- All right, sorry
to spoil the party.

06:19.446 --> 06:20.379
Got a date.

06:20.381 --> 06:21.747
- Well thank you very much.

06:21.749 --> 06:22.749
Oh.

06:24.484 --> 06:26.651
I'm Gina Alexander.

06:28.588 --> 06:30.021
All right guys that's a wrap.

06:30.023 --> 06:31.490
Start loading the gear.

06:31.492 --> 06:32.557
Trent!

06:34.494 --> 06:35.994
- Is she serious?

06:36.696 --> 06:37.829
- Asshole.

06:38.765 --> 06:40.665
The accent was definitely fake.

06:40.667 --> 06:42.901
- He's really from
Australia, I Googled it.

06:42.903 --> 06:44.770
- Well his accent's still fake.

06:44.772 --> 06:46.605
- Hey, Collin, Mitch, wait up.

06:46.607 --> 06:48.006
- Oh, Trent.

06:48.008 --> 06:49.908
Oh I love your accent!

06:49.910 --> 06:54.179
Let's go to Vegas and elope,
you big Australian man.

06:54.181 --> 06:56.515
- I can't believe that you
guys are actually jealous.

06:56.517 --> 06:57.682
- Yeah right.

06:57.684 --> 06:59.684
- Hey Collin, can I take a look?

06:59.686 --> 07:00.952
Thanks.

07:00.954 --> 07:02.821
- My favorite interview
was Concrete Dumptruck.

07:02.823 --> 07:04.456
That guy was sick.

07:04.458 --> 07:06.591
- Yeah I wanna know who names
their kid Concrete Dumptruck.

07:06.593 --> 07:08.193
They should be in prison.

07:10.196 --> 07:12.197
- Hey, when you dumped
the footage on the drive

07:12.199 --> 07:14.065
did you look through
the other interviews?

07:14.067 --> 07:19.204
You were gonna do it, you
said you wanted to take notes.

07:20.006 --> 07:21.106
- Yeah.

07:21.874 --> 07:23.508
- But, um.

07:25.778 --> 07:27.145
Oh my God.

07:27.613 --> 07:28.947
My entire film.

07:28.949 --> 07:31.016
- What are you talking about?

07:31.018 --> 07:34.219
- Everything except the
interview with Trent is gone.

07:34.221 --> 07:36.221
- No, let me see this.

07:36.622 --> 07:38.824
- Oh I am so screwed.

07:45.932 --> 07:47.566
- Uh, it's not a big deal.

07:47.568 --> 07:49.468
We can go back and reshoot it.

07:49.470 --> 07:50.869
- No, they all left.

07:50.871 --> 07:52.704
This is the last show.

07:57.844 --> 07:58.777
- Hi there folks.

07:58.779 --> 07:59.911
I'm here live on the scene

07:59.913 --> 08:02.180
of Gina Alexander's
rock documentary,

08:02.182 --> 08:03.782
where she has managed to delete

08:03.784 --> 08:06.117
almost her entire
footage, every interview.

08:06.119 --> 08:08.186
Gina, tell us how you feel.

08:09.522 --> 08:11.189
Yeah, okay, there
you have it folks.

08:11.191 --> 08:12.924
Another great moment brought
to you by Mitchell J. Pretti,

08:12.926 --> 08:15.166
you can catch more
of my highlights on
my YouTube channel.

08:44.256 --> 08:46.591
- You're Connor's boy, right?

08:46.993 --> 08:48.760
- You from Saxlow?

08:50.663 --> 08:52.230
- Where's your father?

08:57.003 --> 09:00.171
You know he tried to blow up
one of our trucks last week.

09:00.173 --> 09:02.807
Everybody says he's gone crazy.

09:04.710 --> 09:06.678
- Leave us alone.

09:07.914 --> 09:10.916
- We're gonna take this property
one way or another, boy.

09:12.618 --> 09:15.120
I'll turn this whole
town against you!

09:32.104 --> 09:33.738
Donald Connors.

09:35.775 --> 09:39.878
- I think we need to talk.

09:49.055 --> 09:51.323
- I needed that
footage to graduate.

09:51.325 --> 09:55.927
It was only like 10 or 12 of
some of the coolest interviews

09:55.929 --> 09:58.730
of some of the most awesome
bands still alive today.

09:58.732 --> 09:59.931
- Mitch.

10:03.703 --> 10:05.270
- Hey, Gina, don't
feel bad about it okay?

10:05.272 --> 10:07.672
I remember when I was 12,
I lost all my footage.

10:07.674 --> 10:08.640
- Will you just shut up?

10:08.642 --> 10:09.642
- Seriously.

10:10.009 --> 10:11.076
- Enough.

10:13.613 --> 10:14.813
- Awkward.

10:15.615 --> 10:17.649
What mile marker are we at?

10:17.651 --> 10:21.953
- Get off at the next exit, we
can stay at my mom's tonight.

10:21.955 --> 10:23.355
- No, I just wanna
get back okay?

10:23.357 --> 10:25.624
- We're all exhausted,
and I'm starving.

10:25.626 --> 10:27.292
I know a great pub up ahead.

10:28.394 --> 10:29.894
- I'm not hungry.

10:29.896 --> 10:31.830
- Then have a drink.

10:34.734 --> 10:35.800
- Yeah.

10:36.068 --> 10:37.636
- Yeah!

10:37.638 --> 10:40.071
- Welcome to Kern County.

10:40.073 --> 10:43.008
Home of, nothing.

10:58.124 --> 11:01.059
Hey, 10 bucks says the average
sum total of front teeth

11:01.061 --> 11:02.761
in this bar is two point five.

11:02.763 --> 11:04.829
- Dude, this isn't Virginia.

11:06.399 --> 11:07.999
- Just saying.

11:08.334 --> 11:10.101
- All right, let's do this.

11:10.103 --> 11:13.071
- Come on Gina, turn
that frown upside down.

11:13.073 --> 11:14.839
We're getting drunk.

11:17.878 --> 11:19.411
- First round on me.

11:20.346 --> 11:21.446
- IDs?

11:25.818 --> 11:26.885
- Thanks.

11:29.722 --> 11:31.322
- Hold on big guy.

11:31.324 --> 11:32.724
This you?

11:32.726 --> 11:33.458
- Yeah.

11:33.460 --> 11:35.427
- Sure don't look like you.

11:35.429 --> 11:36.828
- I get that a lot.

11:36.830 --> 11:38.463
War changes a man.

11:49.442 --> 11:50.742
- Vietnam?

11:55.214 --> 11:58.416
Okay, maybe we are in Virginia.

12:00.820 --> 12:02.020
Seriously?

12:04.924 --> 12:06.024
- Come on.

12:07.460 --> 12:08.159
- Here.

12:08.161 --> 12:09.360
- Thank you.

12:21.474 --> 12:23.441
In Virginia, if I
divorce my wife,

12:23.443 --> 12:26.511
is she still my mom
or am I an orphan?

12:30.750 --> 12:32.884
Being an orphan must suck.

12:32.886 --> 12:34.486
- Dammit Mitch.

12:34.488 --> 12:36.121
- What?

12:36.956 --> 12:40.024
- I'm gonna go clean off
some of the past 10 hours.

12:41.127 --> 12:42.127
- What?

12:42.995 --> 12:44.529
- She's an orphan.

12:44.531 --> 12:46.798
And you are an idiot.

12:48.234 --> 12:49.868
- How did I not know this?

12:49.870 --> 12:51.503
I've known her
longer than you have.

12:51.505 --> 12:55.206
- Maybe you should talk less
and listen a little more.

13:01.213 --> 13:02.547
- Donald!

13:03.783 --> 13:06.951
- Do you know who belongs
to that black SUV?

13:06.953 --> 13:08.520
- They just came in.

13:14.827 --> 13:15.827
- So where'd you take her?

13:15.829 --> 13:16.961
- I took her to Hardee's.

13:16.963 --> 13:18.429
- That girl lets you
take her anywhere.

13:18.431 --> 13:20.098
How long you guys
been going out?

13:20.100 --> 13:21.032
- Four days?

13:21.034 --> 13:22.333
- That's a record for you.

13:22.335 --> 13:23.434
- It is.

13:23.436 --> 13:25.103
- How've you been Mr. Connors?

13:25.105 --> 13:27.172
I haven't seen you in a while.

13:28.240 --> 13:29.974
- Whisky, bourbon.

13:31.844 --> 13:33.044
- Okay.

13:35.114 --> 13:37.582
- So it would have
been a crime not to.

13:37.584 --> 13:40.318
When they came over,
and it was like...

13:41.921 --> 13:42.921
- Wow.

13:44.490 --> 13:45.990
- I look stupid.

13:45.992 --> 13:48.493
- No, you look great.

13:50.896 --> 13:52.363
- Finish your story.

13:52.365 --> 13:54.232
- No no, it was stupid.

13:54.234 --> 13:56.234
Just, it was dumb.

13:56.236 --> 13:57.335
- Wow.

13:57.337 --> 13:59.237
Mitch Pretti.

13:59.239 --> 14:01.506
If I had only known makeup was
all it took to shut you up,

14:01.508 --> 14:03.241
I would have worn it years ago.

14:03.243 --> 14:05.343
- No you wouldn't have.

14:06.078 --> 14:07.078
- What?

14:07.580 --> 14:09.013
- Nothing.

14:10.182 --> 14:12.116
Guys, can we get the check?

14:12.118 --> 14:14.485
These guys are creeping me out.

14:14.487 --> 14:18.523
- But you, you're the one
that wanted to come here.

14:18.525 --> 14:20.124
- Yeah, I know.

14:20.126 --> 14:21.926
I'll be in the car.

14:23.996 --> 14:25.196
- Really?

14:27.299 --> 14:31.135
- So, two brews
and a pina colada.

14:34.373 --> 14:36.040
- This was his.

14:36.042 --> 14:37.542
- Yeah, right.

14:46.118 --> 14:48.219
- It's been a while, Connors.

14:49.655 --> 14:52.190
Hear you're still holding out.

14:55.060 --> 14:56.494
Look, Donald.

14:57.296 --> 15:00.198
Saxlow was willing to push
her offer up to $600,000.

15:00.200 --> 15:03.201
They won't buy any of us
out until you sign on.

15:03.669 --> 15:05.336
- Not my problem.

15:07.439 --> 15:10.975
- Dammit Donald, you're not
the only one affected by this.

15:10.977 --> 15:13.544
The bank's about
to take my house.

15:13.546 --> 15:17.982
Pete, he hasn't worked
in seven months.

15:17.984 --> 15:20.652
- They killed my son, John.

15:22.254 --> 15:25.423
You think they should
have my land too?

15:28.360 --> 15:30.161
- It was an accident.

15:30.163 --> 15:32.130
It was just an accident.

15:32.132 --> 15:34.265
Do yourself and
your family a favor

15:34.267 --> 15:35.600
and take the money.

15:35.602 --> 15:37.635
You can start over.

15:39.605 --> 15:41.539
- Did they put you up to this?

15:43.409 --> 15:46.144
- I've never seen 'em
before in my life.

15:53.986 --> 15:56.254
Hey, it's been 10 years, Donald.

15:56.256 --> 15:57.588
Just move on.

15:58.724 --> 16:01.092
- Could you move on
if it was your son?

16:01.094 --> 16:03.161
And you see his
killers every day?

16:03.163 --> 16:04.329
Could you?

16:16.308 --> 16:17.709
- What just happened?

16:19.211 --> 16:21.279
- Probably just
fighting over you.

16:21.281 --> 16:22.647
- Shut up.

16:23.282 --> 16:26.451
- Let's finish these
beers and get out of here.

16:26.453 --> 16:28.052
All right, cheers.

17:02.121 --> 17:04.689
Do you remember what happened
last time I was here?

17:04.691 --> 17:06.290
- You mean when my mom started

17:06.291 --> 17:07.724
playing her Joni
Mitchell records

17:07.727 --> 17:09.694
and telling us stories
about LA in the '70s

17:09.695 --> 17:11.529
while forcing you to
model my dad's old clothes

17:11.531 --> 17:12.530
around the living room?

17:12.531 --> 17:13.564
- Yeah.

17:13.566 --> 17:15.032
Let's not do that again.

17:15.035 --> 17:16.467
- I'll do my best.

17:19.239 --> 17:20.637
- Coming!

17:25.244 --> 17:26.411
Oh, Mitch!

17:26.413 --> 17:27.412
- Hi Mom.

17:27.414 --> 17:28.780
- What are you doing here?

17:28.782 --> 17:30.148
Come in, come in.

17:30.150 --> 17:33.151
So happy to see you, hi, hi.

17:33.153 --> 17:36.120
- Hey, you remember
Collin, right?

17:36.122 --> 17:38.723
- Of course I do,
how could I forget?

17:38.725 --> 17:41.559
You look just like
my ex-husband Morty.

17:41.561 --> 17:42.693
Good to see you.

17:42.695 --> 17:45.663
And you must be Gina.

17:45.665 --> 17:49.267
Mitch tells me that
you are making a movie.

17:49.269 --> 17:50.268
- We were.

17:50.270 --> 17:51.636
- We are.

17:53.272 --> 17:55.807
- So guess what guys,
I'm so happy you're here.

17:55.809 --> 17:57.608
I have The Princess Diaries.

17:57.610 --> 18:01.079
- Actually Mom, we're just
hoping to crash for the night.

18:01.081 --> 18:04.582
- Mitch, are you sure your
friends don't wanna play Boggle?

18:06.085 --> 18:08.352
And if not, I have those
Joni Mitchell records.

18:08.354 --> 18:10.088
Do you remember this?

18:10.856 --> 18:12.423
- Oh, I remember.

18:12.425 --> 18:14.292
- It's been a long
day, really long day.

18:14.294 --> 18:15.860
We'll catch up in
the morning, okay?

18:15.862 --> 18:19.464
- Oh okay, my sweet, sweet boy.

18:19.466 --> 18:20.431
- Thanks Mom.

18:20.433 --> 18:21.833
- Oh, I'm so happy you're here.

18:21.835 --> 18:22.767
- Me too.

18:22.769 --> 18:25.236
- Okay, let me take your bags.

18:25.571 --> 18:28.306
Everything's upstairs
that you'll need.

18:28.308 --> 18:29.574
- Come on guys!

18:29.576 --> 18:30.708
- Goodnight.

18:30.710 --> 18:33.177
- Goodnight, so
nice to meet you.

18:34.847 --> 18:38.416
Are you sure that you guys don't
want some milk and cookies?

18:38.418 --> 18:39.717
- We're fine Mom.

18:39.719 --> 18:40.651
- Okay.

18:40.653 --> 18:41.719
But I do have Ben & Jerry's.

18:41.721 --> 18:42.553
- Mom!

18:42.555 --> 18:43.654
- Okay.

18:45.190 --> 18:47.492
I'm glad you're here, sweetie.

18:49.428 --> 18:50.828
- You guys, sorry about my mom.

18:50.830 --> 18:52.763
It's amazing she
survived the '70s.

18:52.765 --> 18:54.332
- I love your mom.

18:57.536 --> 18:59.170
That's so cute.

19:05.144 --> 19:08.346
I didn't realize you had such
a crush on Richard Greico.

19:08.348 --> 19:10.648
- Yeah, it was
kind of a big deal.

19:14.186 --> 19:15.453
- Exactly the same.

19:15.455 --> 19:16.654
It's weird.

19:16.656 --> 19:18.523
- Guys, don't touch
anything, okay?

19:18.525 --> 19:19.790
Just, nothing.

19:20.692 --> 19:21.759
- Karaoke?

19:21.761 --> 19:23.661
- Yeah my mom made me do that.

19:23.663 --> 19:25.496
- There's seven of them.

19:26.231 --> 19:27.298
- Yeah.

19:27.799 --> 19:28.799
- Seven.

19:28.801 --> 19:29.734
- Mhm.

19:29.736 --> 19:31.702
- Why don't you do some for us?

19:31.704 --> 19:34.305
- No, no guys, I'm gonna
go get ready for bed.

19:34.307 --> 19:35.473
- Come on, Danny in Grease.

19:35.475 --> 19:38.709
- You sleep in my room, I'm
gonna sleep in the guest room.

19:38.711 --> 19:39.844
- Funny boy, come on.

19:39.846 --> 19:41.445
- Look guys, it's
not funny, okay?

19:41.447 --> 19:45.483
- Camera out of the face,
this isn't TMZ, goodnight.

19:45.485 --> 19:46.884
- We were only teasing.

19:46.886 --> 19:48.553
- He's sensitive.

19:55.594 --> 19:57.862
I will sleep on the floor.

19:59.565 --> 20:00.531
- Okay.

20:00.533 --> 20:02.233
- I'll take that.

20:33.765 --> 20:34.799
- Hey.

20:42.808 --> 20:44.375
You awake?

20:48.513 --> 20:50.448
- Now I am.

20:52.017 --> 20:53.517
What's up?

20:54.386 --> 20:55.920
- I can't sleep.

20:59.391 --> 21:02.026
- Think about The Notebook.

21:03.028 --> 21:05.730
- Shut up, that's
my favorite movie.

21:05.732 --> 21:07.298
- Yeah, I know.

21:10.736 --> 21:12.870
- You can come up
here if you want.

21:12.872 --> 21:15.806
The floor must not
be that comfortable.

21:16.441 --> 21:17.408
- Why?

21:17.410 --> 21:19.877
So you can take advantage of me?

21:19.879 --> 21:21.946
- Fine, stay down there.

21:23.315 --> 21:26.784
- Shh, I'm trying to
think about The Notebook.

21:53.545 --> 21:56.981
So this is what a
mattress feels like.

22:03.488 --> 22:04.689
What's wrong?

22:05.924 --> 22:08.726
You still thinking
about the footage?

22:12.431 --> 22:14.532
- It's a frikkin' disaster.

22:17.436 --> 22:20.771
- You don't think Steven
Spielberg ever made mistakes?

22:23.008 --> 22:25.343
Look, when we get back to LA,

22:25.345 --> 22:28.679
I will help you shoot that
other project you wanted to do.

22:31.383 --> 22:32.750
- You're really sweet to me.

22:32.752 --> 22:34.452
- Shh, whoa.

22:34.686 --> 22:37.955
I don't wanna ruin my
bad boy image, you know?

22:37.957 --> 22:39.557
People talk.

22:56.942 --> 22:58.075
Sorry.

23:00.879 --> 23:02.079
- I, uh...

24:58.563 --> 25:00.698
- What the fuck have you done?

25:01.633 --> 25:03.033
- 10 years now.

25:05.170 --> 25:08.772
10 years I've been telling
you people to stay away,

25:08.774 --> 25:10.774
but you keep coming back.

25:11.109 --> 25:14.044
You fucking murdered my son!

25:14.279 --> 25:17.982
You keep harassing my family.

25:17.984 --> 25:20.518
You know, there comes a time

25:20.520 --> 25:23.053
when a man can't
take it anymore.

25:23.055 --> 25:25.823
When a man is no
longer responsible

25:25.825 --> 25:29.560
for his actions to
protect what's his.

25:29.562 --> 25:31.929
A man has his limits!

25:34.165 --> 25:37.301
- Do you have any idea
